  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What is the best way to clean house windows?",
  "response": "Cleaning house windows effectively involves a few steps to ensure they are streak-free and sparkling. Here's a comprehensive guide:\n\n### Materials Needed:\n- Bucket\n- Water\n- Dish soap or a window cleaning solution\n- Vinegar (optional)\n- Microfiber cloths or lint-free towels\n- Sponge or soft brush\n- Squeegee\n- Newspaper or paper towels (optional)\n- Extension pole (for high windows)\n\n### Steps:\n\n1. **Preparation**:\n   - Choose a cloudy day to clean windows. Direct sunlight can cause the cleaning solution to dry too quickly, leaving streaks.\n   - Ensure you have all the necessary materials ready.\n\n2. **Dust and Remove Cobwebs**:\n   - Use a dry microfiber cloth or a duster to remove dust and cobwebs from the window frames and sills.\n\n3. **Prepare Cleaning Solution**:\n   - Mix a few drops of dish soap in a bucket of warm water. Alternatively, you can mix equal parts vinegar and water for a natural cleaning solution.\n\n4. **Initial Cleaning**:\n   - Dip a sponge or soft brush into the cleaning solution and scrub the window to remove dirt and grime. Pay special attention to stubborn spots.\n\n5. **Rinse**:\n   - Rinse the window with clean water to remove the soap residue. You can use a hose for exterior windows or a bucket of clean water for interior windows.\n\n6. **Squeegee Technique**:\n   - Starting at the top corner, pull the squeegee down in a straight line. Wipe the squeegee blade with a clean cloth after each pass to avoid streaks.\n   - Continue this process, slightly overlapping each stroke, until the entire window is clean.\n\n7. **Dry and Polish**:\n   - Use a microfiber cloth or lint-free towel to wipe any remaining water from the edges and corners of the window.\n   - For an extra polish, use crumpled newspaper or paper towels to buff the glass to a shine.\n\n8. **Final Touches**:\n   - Clean the window frames and sills with a damp cloth and dry them thoroughly.\n   - If your windows are particularly dirty, you might need to repeat the process.\n\n### Tips:\n- For high windows, use an extension pole with a squeegee attachment.\n- Avoid using abrasive materials that can scratch the glass.\n- Regular cleaning (at least twice a year) helps maintain the clarity and cleanliness of your windows.\n\nFollowing these steps will help you achieve clean, streak-free windows that enhance the appearance of your home.",
